race.comment: The promising LARADO (8) made it three wins from four when he just arrived in time here at this trip a fortnight ago. Tackles a better race today but there is plenty of scope for improvement. MOONHAVEN (7) settled midfield and was just fair through the line when resuming over today's journey at the Sunshine Coast last start. Can do better with the blinkers back on. Last start Grafton winner ROYAL COMMODORE (6) will find this tougher but his record at the trip is outstanding. PORT ERIN (3) did his best work late on resuming at Sunshine Coast. Will be fitter for that outing and has won second up in the past.
